The paper deals with handwritten character recognition using deep learning neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. The use of appropriate activation function and regularization layer also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves processing natural language, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or computational linguistics (cs.CL).
